description: From Middle English gaynsetten, yensetten (also aȝeynesetten (“to oppose”)), equivalent to gain- +‎ set. Cognate with archaic German gegensetzen (“to oppose”) (whence entgegensetzen), German Gegensatz (“opposition”).

verbs.description: gainset (third-person singular simple present gainsets, present participle gainsetting, simple past and past participle gainset)

entries.meaning: (transitive, rare, dialectal or archaic) To set over against; oppose.
